DATA CLOUD
Set Up Connected App for DBeaver

Create a connected app to connect DBeaver to Data Cloud through the Java Database Connectivity Driver (JDBC).

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: All Editions supported by Data Cloud. See Data Cloud edition availability.
Log in to Salesforce. From Setup, enter Apps in the Quick Find box, and select App Manager.
Click New Connected App.
VALUE	DESCRIPTION
Connected App Name	Data Cloud DBeaver Connection.
API Name	

Data_Cloud_DBeaver_Connection

NOTE You can also choose to retain the name populated by default.

Contact Email	Enter your email address.
In the API (Enable OAuth Settings) area of the page, select Enable OAuth Settings.
Enter the following callback URLs.
http://localhost:55555/Callback
http://localhost:55556/Callback
http://localhost:55557/Callback
http://localhost:55558/Callback
http://localhost:55559/Callback
Select the following OAuth scopes to define permissions for the connected app.
VALUE	DESCRIPTION
Manage user data via APIs	Allows access to the current, logged-in user’s account using APIs, such as REST API and Bulk API 2.0. This scope also includes chatter_api, which allows access to Connect REST API resources.
Manage Data Cloud profile data	Allows access to Data Cloud REST API data. Use this scope to manage profile records.
Perform ANSI SQL queries on Data Cloud data (cdp_query_api)	Allows ANSI SQL queries of Data Cloud data on behalf of the user.
Perform requests at any time	

Allows a refresh token to be returned when the requesting client is eligible to receive one. With a refresh token, the app can interact with the user’s data while the user is offline. This token is synonymous with requesting.

offline_access
NOTE You can add further scopes if necessary.
Click Save. Next click Continue.
You need consumer keys for establishing a connection through DBeaver.
Under Data Cloud DBeaver Connection connected app, click Manage Consumer Details. Copy the consumer key and consumer secret.
In your DBeaver application, click Driver Settings, navigate to Driver Properties.
Add the clientId and clientSecret with the consumer key and consumer secret.
Click Finish.
